  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Portugal: Technical Support to the High Commission for Migration to Improve the Response of National Centres for Migrant Integration by Assessing and Evaluating their Services and Operations</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at contributing to improved integration of migrants in Portugal by providing technical support to the High Commission for Migration. In particular, the project will assess the response provided by the National Centres for Migrant Integration (CNAIMs) operating in Lisbon, Porto, and Faro. In order to achieve this aim, the project will evaluate three key areas that structure the CNAIMs&#x2019; overall integrated response to migrant needs: 1) Relevance and effectiveness of the services provided by the CNAIMs in Lisbon, Porto and Faro; 2) Coordination and monitoring mechanisms of CNAIMs vis-&#xE0;-vis the Local Centres for Migrant Integration; and 3) Sociocultural mediation model operating at the CNAIMS. The project will propose recommendations for improvement of the services provided to migrants vis-avis changing migratory, policy and institutional scenarios in Portugal.</narrative>
  </description>
